THE PASS:
1. DIFF: find all .md files created or modified in the last 24 hours (exclude .obsidian/, 07_Archive/, _lint.md reports).
2. FRONTMATTER: for each new/modified note missing frontmatter, add it per vault conventions (type, status, tags; date for dated entries; related: [[...]] where obvious). Match existing tag hierarchy (decision/, phase/, production/, preference/, session/) — check sibling files before inventing a new tag family.
3. CONNECT: for each new note, search the vault for related existing notes (same topic, same video number, same project, same decision thread) and add [[wikilinks]] in both directions where natural. Prioritize: session digests ↔ the decisions/designs/files they describe; new deliverables ↔ Launch_Runway.md and the build queues; new decisions ↔ the preference/pattern notes they touch.
4. MOC FRESHNESS: if a new canonical doc landed, add it to the right section of _MAP/Vault_MOC.md and bump its "last touched" footer.
5. NON-OBVIOUS CONNECTIONS: surface up to 3 genuinely non-obvious connections between recent notes and older vault content. Apply the safe ones as wikilinks; describe them in the report.
6. DECISION QUEUE MAINTENANCE (per Decisions_Log/2026-06-10_Default_Action_Autonomy.md): open 06_CEO/Decision_Queue.md. (a) Increment "Days pending" on every ⏳ open row. (b) For any AUTO-class row past deadline, set status to "✅ PROCEEDING (default, YYYY-MM-DD)" and list it prominently in your report — the next interactive session executes the default. (c) NEVER auto-proceed 💰/📤/🎨/⚖️ rows — mark "🔁 re-surfaced" instead. (d) Add rows for any new pending-Steve decisions found in the last 24h of vault writes (class it, propose default + 72-hr deadline).
7. INBOX HYGIENE (contract in INBOX.md header, established 2026-06-10): INBOX must stay ≤150 lines, actions + pointers only. (a) Move any dated digest/narrative section older than 7 days to INBOX_Archive.md (append under a dated heading; content is preserved there — this move is contracted, not a deletion). (b) Move ✅-completed items older than 7 days the same way. (c) If any agent re-introduced digest narration, replace it with a one-line pointer to its session digest. (d) Report the resulting line count; if >150 after cleanup, flag it.
8. TODO REGEN (Sundays only, or if TODO.md's header date is >8 days old): regenerate TODO.md from the canonical sources per its header contract — INBOX TODAY/THIS WEEK + Decision_Queue rows + Launch_Runway statuses + Launch_Scorecard top table + the E-queues in 06_CEO/Designs/. Keep the same section skeleton (North star / Critical path / Production / Pending decisions / Engineering / Infra state / Recently closed). Keep it ≤80 lines — it loads into the daemon's prompt.
9. STEVE_CONTEXT BUMP DISCIPLINE (flag-only, never edit that file): if a new date-bump in STEVE_CONTEXT.md exceeds ~200 words, note it in your report as a bridge-rotation candidate (the ≤150-word + pointer-to-bridge rule, audit finding #4). Claude Code owns the fix.

REPORT: append the section heading EXACTLY "## 🌿 Vault gardener (4:10 AM)" to today's daily note at _Iris_Memory/Daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (create from 01_Operating_Docs/Templates/Daily_Note_Template.md if missing). DO NOT rename that heading — the 5:00 AM pre-brief Pass 16 empty-alarm parses it character-for-character. ~10 lines max: files touched, links added, MOC updates, non-obvious connections, Decision Queue changes, INBOX line count + archived sections, TODO regen (if run), any discipline flags. If nothing changed in 24h and no deadlines/hygiene triggers hit, write one line saying so and stop — do not invent work.

